Dataset Name: Premier League Matches (2010–2020)

Description:
The Premier League Matches dataset contains detailed statistics for football matches
played between 2010 and 2020. Each record represents a single match and includes
performance metrics for both the home and away teams. The dataset captures key
aspects of gameplay such as passing, possession, shots, fouls, and defensive actions,
providing a comprehensive view of match dynamics.


Match Structure:
Each row corresponds to one match and includes:
- General match information (season, date, teams)
- Home team statistics
- Away team statistics
- Final match outcome


Key Features:
The dataset includes numerical and categorical features such as:
- Passing and possession metrics
- Offensive statistics (shots, shots on target, goals)
- Defensive actions (tackles, clearances)
- Discipline indicators (fouls, yellow/red cards)


Outcome Representation:
Match results are defined using:
- goal_home_ft: goals scored by the home team
- goal_away_ft: goals scored by the away team
- sg_match_ft: goal difference (home − away)
- result: final outcome (Home Win, Draw, Away Win)


Class Distribution:
- Home Wins: majority of matches
- Away Wins: slightly fewer than home wins
- Draws: least frequent outcome


Notes:
The dataset supports a wide range of analytical tasks, including performance analysis,
trend exploration, and predictive modeling. It is well-suited for SQL-based analytics
and can be extended to machine learning applications such as match outcome prediction.
